The Retired Officers Association (TROA) is one chapter I have found that is mostly Vietnam Vets.  They are very active, cautious recruiters and have monthly meetings in most locations.  The chaters I have seen do not normally have their own building, but have an agreement to use some locate establishment.<br><br>
I believe their is an organization comprised of NCOs.<br><br>
The sad part is I do not see open enrollment from any of these.  More like a private social club with invited membership only.  I have declined memebrship on several occassions for this reason.<br><br>
Someday soon we will be the only ones left.  Will we let the Gulf War boys give us the cold shoulder also or will we take the lead and move out?  A group who wants something usually makes it happen.
